\section{The Third Definitive Issue}

(1882-1883)

Early in 1882 a new type of paper was introduced for the various colonies. 
This paper was watermarked with a crown and CA (Crown Agents) in place 
of the Crown CC (Crown Colony) which had been in use since about 1863.

\ph[30%]{../cape-of-good-hope/ADHESIVES/rectangulars-seated-hope/Three_Pence.png}{
